ource src=&quot;//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/transcoded/2/25/TEDxDelft_3D_scanning_of_the_Staalmeesters.webm/TEDxDelft_3D_scanning_of_the_Staalmeesters.webm.240p.webm&quot; type=&quot;video/webm; codecs=&amp;quot;vp8, vorbis&amp;quot;&quot; data-title=&quot;Small WebM (240P)&quot; data-shorttitle=&quot;WebM 240P&quot; data-transcodekey=&quot;240p.webm&quot; data-width=&quot;426&quot; data-height=&quot;240&quot; data-bandwidth=&quot;324856&quot; data-framerate=&quot;25&quot;/&gt;&lt;source src=&quot;//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/transcoded/2/25/TEDxDelft_3D_scanning_of_the_Staalmeesters.webm/TEDxDelft_3D_scanning_of_the_Staalmeesters.webm.240p.ogv&quot; type=&quot;video/ogg; codecs=&amp;quot;theora, vorbis&amp;quot;&quot; data-title=&quot;Small Ogg video (240P)&quot; data-shorttitle=&quot;Ogg 240P&quot; data-transcodekey=&quot;240p.ogv&quot; data-width=&quot;426&quot; data-height=&quot;240&quot; data-bandwidth=&quot;537624&quot; data-framerate=&quot;60&quot;/&gt;&lt;source src=&quot;//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/transcoded/2/25/TEDxDelft_3D_scanning_of_the_Staalmeesters.webm/TEDxDelft_3D_scanning_of_the_Staalmeesters.webm.360p.webm&quot; type=&quot;video/webm; codecs=&amp;quot;vp8, vorbis&amp;quot;&quot; data-title=&quot;WebM (360P)&quot; data-shorttitle=&quot;WebM 360P&quot; data-transcodekey=&quot;360p.webm&quot; data-width=&quot;640&quot; data-height=&quot;360&quot; data-bandwidth=&quot;574272&quot; data-framerate=&quot;25&quot;/&gt;&lt;source src=&quot;//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/transcoded/2/25/TEDxDelft_3D_scanning_of_the_Staalmeesters.webm/TEDxDelft_3D_scanning_of_the_Staalmeesters.webm.360p.ogv&quot; type=&quot;video/ogg; codecs=&amp;quot;theora, vorbis&amp;quot;&quot; data-title=&quot;Ogg video (360P)&quot; data-shorttitle=&quot;Ogg 360P&quot; data-transcodekey=&quot;360p.ogv&quot; data-width=&quot;640&quot; data-height=&quot;360&quot; data-bandwidth=&quot;1069608&quot; data-framerate=&quot;60&quot;/&gt;&lt;/video&gt;&lt;/div&gt;"><img alt="File:TEDxDelft 3D scanning of the Staalmeesters.webm" style="width:220px;height:124px" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/25/TEDxDelft_3D_scanning_of_the_Staalmeesters.webm/220px--TEDxDelft_3D_scanning_of_the_Staalmeesters.webm.jpg" /><a href="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/25/TEDxDelft_3D_scanning_of_the_Staalmeesters.webm" title="Play media" target="new"><span class="play-btn-large"><span class="mw-tmh-playtext">Play media</span></span></a></div>\n<div class="thumbcaption">\n<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:TEDxDelft_3D_scanning_of_the_Staalmeesters.webm" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>\n3D scanning of the <a href="/wiki/Rembrandt" title="Rembrandt">Rembrandt</a>-painting <a href="/wiki/Syndics_of_the_Drapers%27_Guild" title="Syndics of the Drapers\' Guild">Syndics of the Drapers\' Guild</a>.</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p><b>X-ray fluorescence</b> (<b>XRF</b>) is the emission of characteristic "secondary" (or fluorescent) <a href="/wiki/X-rays" class="mw-redirect" title="X-rays">X-rays</a> from a material that has been excited by bombarding with high-energy X-rays or <a href="/wiki/Gamma_rays" class="mw-redirect" title="Gamma rays">gamma rays</a>. The phenomenon is widely used for <a href="/wiki/Elemental_analysis" title="Elemental analysis">elemental analysis</a> and <a href="/wiki/Analytical_chemistry" title="Analytical chemistry">chemical analysis</a>, particularly in the investigation of <a href="/wiki/Metal" title="Metal">metals</a>, <a href="/wiki/Glass" title="Glass">glass</a>, <a href="/wiki/Ceramic" title="Ceramic">ceramics</a> and building materials, and for research in <a href="/wiki/Geochemistry" title="Geochemistry">geochemistry</a>, <a href="/wiki/Forensic_science" title="Forensic science">forensic science</a>, <a href="/wiki/Archaeology" title="Archaeology">archaeology</a> and art objects<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1">[1]</a></sup> such as <a href="/wiki/Paintings" class="mw-redirect" title="Paintings">paintings</a><sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2">[2]</a></sup> and <a href="/wiki/Murals" class="mw-redirect" title="Murals">murals</a>.</p>\n<p></p>\n<div id="toc" class="toc">\n<div class="toctitle">\n<h2>Contents</h2>\n</div>\n<ul>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-1"><a href="#Underlying_physics"><span class="tocnumber">1</span> <span class="toctext">Underlying physics</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-2"><a href="#Characteristic_radiation"><span class="tocnumber">1.1</span> <span class="toctext">Characteristic radiation</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-3"><a href="#Primary_radiation"><span class="tocnumber">1.2</span> <span class="toctext">Primary radiation</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-4"><a href="#Dispersion"><span class="tocnumber">1.3</span> <span class="toctext">Dispersion</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-5"><a href="#Detection"><span class="tocnumber">1.4</span> <span class="toctext">Detection</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-6"><a href="#X-ray_intensity"><span class="tocnumber">1.5</span> <span class="toctext">X-ray intensity</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-7"><a href="#Chemical_analysis"><span class="tocnumber">2</span> <span class="toctext">Chemical analysis</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-8"><a href="#Energy_dispersive_spectrometry"><span class="tocnumber">2.1</span> <span class="toctext">Energy dispersive spectrometry</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class="toclevel-3 tocsection-9"><a href="#Si.28Li.29_detectors"><span class="tocnumber">2.1.1</span> <span class="toctext">Si(Li) detectors</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-3 tocsection-10"><a href="#Wafer_detectors"><span class="tocnumber">2.1.2</span> <span class="toctext">Wafer detectors</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-3 tocsection-11"><a href="#Amplifiers"><span class="tocnumber">